header.gameNote: NCAA Women's Championship pres. by Capital One - River Walk Region - Final

videos.headline: Bueckers scores on UConn's opening possession
videos.description: Paige Bueckers goes baseline and hits the fadeaway jumper to get UConn off to a hot start.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Bueckers scores on UConn's opening possession) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: NaLyssa Smith converts the steal into a layup
videos.description: Baylor's NaLyssa Smith picks off Christyn Williams' pass and races for the layup to end the first quarter.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (NaLyssa Smith converts the steal into a layup) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Carrington meets Williams at the basket with a huge block
videos.description: Baylor's DiJonai Carrington denies Christyn Williams' chance at a layup.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Carrington meets Williams at the basket with a huge block) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Bueckers slices through Baylor's defense for a layup
videos.description: Paige Bueckers effortlessly drives through traffic for the lay-in.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Bueckers slices through Baylor's defense for a layup) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Carrington hyped after and-1 bucket
videos.description: DiJonai Carrington can't contain her excitement after absorbing contact for the basket, plus the foul.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Carrington hyped after and-1 bucket) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Kim Mulkey gets fired up after Baylor's tip-in
videos.description: NaLyssa Smith runs in to clean up DiJonai Carrington's miss with a tip-in shot and coach Kim Mulkey loves it.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Kim Mulkey gets fired up after Baylor's tip-in) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Bueckers' back-to-back buckets add to UConn's 17-0 run
videos.description: Paige Bueckers catches fire and hits big shots on consecutive possessions to extend UConn's lead.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Bueckers' back-to-back buckets add to UConn's 17-0 run) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: UConn stops Baylor after controversial no-call
videos.description: Aaliyah Edwards gets a huge block on DiJonai Carrington to help UConn seal the win vs. Baylor and advance to the Final Four.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (UConn stops Baylor on wild sequence in closing seconds) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Bueckers' 28 points lead UConn to its 13th consecutive Final Four
videos.description: Paige Bueckers goes off for 28 points in the Elite Eight to help the No. 1-seeded Huskies outlast No. 2 Baylor 69-67.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Highlight (Bueckers' 28 points lead UConn to its 13th consecutive Final Four) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Players interrupt Geno's interview to douse him in confetti
videos.description: Geno Auriemma is caught off guard when his players cover him in confetti mid-interview after UConn's big win vs. Baylor to advance to the Final Four.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Interview (Players interrupt Geno's interview to douse him in confetti) 2021/3/29

videos.headline: DiDi Richards exits the game with thigh injury
videos.description: Baylor's DiDi Richards falls to the floor in pain while driving, holding her thigh and exits the game.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (DiDi Richards exits the game with thigh injury) 2021/3/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Mulkey on controversial ending: I saw a foul
videos.description: Baylor coach Kim Mulkey disagrees with the no-foul call at the end of the Baylor vs. UConn matchup.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Presser (Mulkey on controversial ending: I saw a foul) 2021/3/29

videos.headline: Mulkey wants NCAA to 'dump' COVID-19 testing for men's and women's Final Four
videos.description: Baylor coach Kim Mulkey suggests the NCAA stop testing the players for COVID-19 ahead of the men's and women's Final Four.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Presser (Mulkey wants NCAA to 'dump' COVID-19 testing for men's and women's Final Four) 2021/3/29

videos.headline: UConn survives controversial finale to advance to Final Four
videos.description: UConn holds on after a controversial no-foul call to advance past Baylor and into the Final Four.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCW Highlight (UConn survives controversial finale to advance to Final Four) 2021/03/30 ESHEET SC
